      <section eId="sec_1836_E">
        <num>1836-E</num>
        <heading>Loan agreements</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_1836_E__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>and</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_1836_E__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>\nof subdivision two of section eighteen hundred three and paragraph</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_1836_E__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>\nof subdivision seven of section eighteen hundred twenty-three of this\nchapter.\n  3. The local development corporation may not enter into any loan\nagreement unless the authority determines through an appropriate method\nthat there is reasonable assurance of repayment. The authority shall\nestablish such requirements or terms as it may deem necessary or\ndesirable to secure the repayment of the loan and to protect the\ninterests of the authority and the holders of its bonds.\n  4. Subject to the requirements of this subtitle, the authority is\nauthorized to determine the form and substance of any loan agreement\nmade pursuant to this subtitle.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
